ild(t,a);var a=e.createElement("p"),n=e.createTextNode('\n	“There is always some amount of luck that is involved with any exit but you have to put in the hard work to make sure the company is in a position to succeed. At Gigle we had an incredible engineering team that focused on leading edge manufacturing technologies and true product differentiation and had just the right timing. Starting with an all star team and developing a product that had market fit was key. Then, it was only a matter of time before a company like Broadcom would want to acquire us to incorporate our home networking technology into their product portfolio. This happened to align with our series C round of funding, which was good timing."\n');e.appendChild(a,n),e.appendChild(t,a);var a=e.createTextNode("\n\n");e.appendChild(t,a);var a=e.createElement("h5");e.setAttribute(a,"class","margin-top");var n=e.createTextNode("Myth 1: I need a large sales team to succeed");e.appendChild(a,n),e.appendChild(t,a);var a=e.createTextNode("\n");e.appendChild(t,a);var a=e.createElement("p"),n=e.createTextNode("\n	“Gigle’s sales team only reached a total of 4 before we were acquired for $83 million. You do not need a large sales team to succeed, and we only had 4 for a hardware company. With a SaaS or app-focused startup, you can get by with even less people. ”\n");e.appendChild(a,n),e.appendChild(t,a);var a=e.createTextNode("\n\n");e.appendChild(t,a);var a=e.createElement("h5"),n=e.createTextNode("Myth 2: I am not a sales person, therefore I cannot sell");e.appendChild(a,n),e.appendChild(t,a);var a=e.createTextNode("\n\n");e.appendChild(t,a);var a=e.createElement("p"),n=e.createTextNode("\n	“As a startup founder, you are always selling your vision internally to your team. Selling that vision to the customer is not so different. All the co-founders need to take a part in selling the product to customers.  Your passion for the market and product will help overcome any sales skill you may lack.”\n");e.appendChild